      "id": 10,
      "options": {
        "content": "<div style=\"padding:18px 22px;\">\n  <h1 style=\"margin:0 0 8px 0; font-size:22px; font-weight:600; color:#e5e7eb; letter-spacing:-0.01em;\">Who's using SupportBot \u2014 and what is it costing?</h1>\n  <p style=\"margin:0 0 12px 0; color:#a3a3a3; font-size:14px; max-width:960px; line-height:1.55;\">\n    ACME's internal SupportBot routes every employee chat through <code style=\"background:#1f1f1f; padding:1px 5px; border-radius:3px; color:#fbbf24;\">sb-router</code> (intent classifier) to one of nine specialists (<code style=\"background:#1f1f1f; padding:1px 5px; border-radius:3px; color:#fbbf24;\">sb-hr-info</code>, <code style=\"background:#1f1f1f; padding:1px 5px; border-radius:3px; color:#fbbf24;\">sb-it-troubleshoot</code>, <code style=\"background:#1f1f1f; padding:1px 5px; border-radius:3px; color:#fbbf24;\">sb-policy-finder</code>, \u2026). AI is usage-priced, so a handful of heavy users or abusers can swing the monthly bill 10\u00d7 while the average employee is a rounding error. <b style=\"color:#e5e7eb;\">This view ranks the top 10 internal users by 24h cost</b> and shows which agents they're hitting.\n  </p>\n  <div style=\"display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(3, 1fr); gap:14px; font-size:13px; color:#d4d4d4; line-height:1.5;\">\n    <div><span style=\"color:#8b5cf6; font-weight:700;\">\u2460 Leaderboard</span> \u2014 calls, tokens, 24h\u00a0cost, projected 30d cost, and waste % (low-quality calls / total). Sorted by spend.</div>\n    <div><span style=\"color:#8b5cf6; font-weight:700;\">\u2461 Per-user agent mix</span> \u2014 stacked tokens by sb-* specialist. Outliers in one agent often indicate misuse or repetitive misuse patterns.</div>\n    <div><span style=\"color:#8b5cf6; font-weight:700;\">\u2462 Time trends</span> \u2014 cost/hour and calls/min. Spikes outside business hours = paste-bombs (Priya), injection probes (Eric), or exfil attempts (Tim).</div>\n  </div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:12px; font-size:12px; color:#737373;\">Tip: pick a single user from the <b>User</b> dropdown to scope the whole dashboard. Scope is hard-pinned to <code style=\"background:#1f1f1f; padding:1px 5px; border-radius:3px; color:#a3a3a3;\">ai_o11y_specialist=~\"sb-.*\"</code> so only SupportBot traffic counts.</div>\n</div>",
        "mode": "html"
      },
      "title": "",
      "transparent": true,
      "type": "text"
    },
